gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 145, Warriors 144
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Warriors, 145-144, in double-overtime. LeBron James recorded 36 points, a career-high 20 rebounds and 12 assists for the Lakers, while Anthony Davis (29 points, 13 rebounds, four blocks) and DAngelo Russell (28 points, five assists, five 3PM) added a combined 57 points in the victory. Stephen Curry tallied a season-high 46 point and nine 3PM for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 24-23 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 19-24.
